The Association of National Olympic Committees of Africa (ANOCA) and a global network organization for the promotion of clean environment – Let’s Do It World (LDIW), in collaboration with other interest groups are organizing the World Clean-up Day (WCD). The Association of National Olympic Committees of Africa (ANOCA) is encouraging all National Olympic Committees of Africa to join other stakeholders of interest such as local municipalities, Ministries of Health, waste managers and departments of environment in celebrating the day. Engr. Habu Gumel, President, Nigeria Olympic Committee (NOC)  who is also the Chairman of ANOCA’s Jury for the organization of the World Clean-up Day, said the best performing NOC will be awarded a prize. The World Clean-up Day is scheduled to take place tomorrow at the National Stadium in Surulere, Lagos.